A consultant with Principal Partner Conanic Associates, Arch Shehu Ahmed Tukur has said that the proposed Karu Mega Bus Terminal project would end the perennial traffic congestion on Abuja-Keffi road. Tukur, who stated this when he spoke with newsmen, noted that the traffic congestion on the road has affected the Muhammadu Buhari International Market in Karu. He noted that there are more than 20 motor parks in Karu, just as he maintained that to have a sound traffic management that illegal motor parks must be relocated to reduce the traffic congestion on the road. Also speaking, the senior special assistant to the Nasarawa State governor on developmental control, Arch Stanly Buba, said that the proposed bus terminal project is an attempt to bring sanity to the area. “It is more like a train station where there is arrival and departure and various categories. The consultants and contractors have been carefully selected; they are people who have worked in bringing development to the state. “We will look out for mistakes that have occurred in the past administration and then targets that have been set that have not been achieved. Our focus is trying to raise revenue for the government and also having a planned environment where regulations are being respected.”